					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><span style="font-size: 85%; line-height: normal"><em>note: i'm discussing the <strong>ntsc standards</strong>, as 1 cpu cycle = 3 ppu dots.</em></span><br />For the 1st time, I played with the PPU timing. What's up? Well, there's an unfinished discussion about clocking the PPU (running for 3 cycles) before or after a CPU clock. Since a few games have flickering scorebars, I decided to play with the PPU timing. For my surprise, things are &quot;completely fixed&quot; when the number of PPU cycles alternates between 3 and 2 for every CPU cycle. <br /><br />Anything about it?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

